news.title: BCD Group appoints Ashwinder R. Singh as vice chairman and CEO
news.para: The current managing director, Angad Singh Bedi has been elevated to chairman and managing director.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body releases list of top 100 property tax defaulters
news.para: ​​Notable defaulters on the list include Bengaluru Metropolitan Transport Corporation, Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation, Bengaluru Metropolitan Rail Corporation Limited, the Transport Department, and the Karnataka Housing Board, among others.

news.title: Delhi: Vasant Kunj residents protest against new housing complex
news.para: Rohit Sejwal, a representative of the housing project, however, claimed that all necessary permissions had been acquired and there was no violation of regulations.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body to crack down on illegal layouts
news.para: According to sources, many builders who received initial approval from Huda to develop layouts failed to obtain the necessary Development Completion Certificates (CC) but proceeded to sell plots without them.

news.title: The Chapter to invest Rs 850 crore in luxury villas across leisure destinations
news.para: The company, part of the Isprava Group, has acquired over 100 acres in four key locations—Goa, Alibaug, Karjat and Kasauli—with an initial investment of Rs 450 crore as part of this strategic growth plan.

news.title: Adani Group to set up two million tonne cement grinding unit in Guna
news.para: The event here attracted investments from large industries totalling Rs 8,000 crore across various sectors, with expected employment generation of 35,000 and over 2,500 MSMEs expressed intent to invest Rs 5,000 crore, an official said.

news.title: Net office leasing to grow 10-12% to 41-43 million sq ft in FY25: Report
news.para: Net leasing will pick up pace this fiscal after four years of gradual recovery, while commercial office supply is expected to remain high, similar to last fiscal, the report said.

news.title: NGT issues notices over illegal construction at Ansals Aravali Retreat
news.para: The bench of NGT chairperson Prakash Shrivastava and expert member Dr A Senthil Vel on Aug 23 directed Haryana chief secretary, principal chief conservator of forest, Haryana space application center and Gurgaon district magistrate to respond at least a week before the next date of hearing on Dec 3.

news.title: EOW initiates inquiry into allegations against Madhya Pradesh RERA chairman
news.para: Key issues include manipulation of recruitment processes and irregular property purchases. Srivastava is accused of ignoring age restrictions and improper property acquisitions amid ongoing investigations.MP EOW initiates inquiry into allegations against Madhya Pradesh RERA chairmanMP RERA chief under EOW probe for alleged corruption, land deal

news.title: Bombay HC grants bail to ABIL Group's founder in PMLA case
news.para: ​​Bhosale, chairman and founder of ABIL Group, was arrested by the Enforcement Directorate in June 2022. He had been initially arrested by the CBI in a corruption case, and obtained bail from the high court in that case in May.

news.title: MHADA reduces price by 10-25% on 370 surplus tenements in Mumbai board lottery
news.para: Atul Save, housing minister, Maharashtra while giving details about the reductions informed that a 25% cut for the economically weaker section (EWS), 20% for the low-income group (LIG), 15% for the middle-income group (MIG), and 10% for the high-income group (HIG) is being extended.

news.title: Germany: Aroundtown's loss narrows to $481.5 million in Q2 2024
news.para: Aroundtown, one of the largest listed landlords in the country, said its second-quarter loss narrowed to 432 million euros ($481.5 million) from 1.27 billion a year earlier.

news.title: Can't slap stamp duty on sale agreement when deed is executed: Karnataka HC
news.para: The petitioners, the plaintiffs in the partition suit, claimed that there is already a sale deed and they produced the agreement of sale only as evidence in support of their claim in that particular partition suit to demonstrate that they are in possession.

news.title: China's Bank of Communications warns of developers' bad debts as profit dips
news.para: The bank's Chief Risk Officer Liu Jianjun said the cash flow of some real estate firms has not fully recovered, so BoCom "still faces certain pressures from non-performing loans in related lending businesses".

news.title: Union cabinet approves 12 new industrial cities with an outlay of Rs 28,602 crore
news.para: These industrial areas will be located in Khurpia in Uttrakhand, Rajpura-Patiala in Punjab, Dighi in Maharashtra, Palakkad in Kerala, Agra and Prayagraj in UP, Gaya in Bihar, Zaheerabad in Telangana, Orvakal and Kopparthy in AP, and Jodhpur-Pali in Rajasthan.

news.title: Circle rates of key Ayodhya locations likely to see 200% rise
news.para: The rates here were revised last in 2017. The final rate list that would offer clarity to the interested buyers on the quantum of the hike would be available publicly on Wednesday or Thursday.

news.title: Sweden's SBB posts $343.79 million loss in Q2 2024
news.para: The landlord, which racked up debt buying properties such as schools and hospitals, reported an April-June loss before tax of 3.5 billion Swedish crowns ($343.79 million), smaller than a revised 10 billion crown loss a year earlier.

news.title: Office leasing in top eight cities expected to cross 80 million sq ft in 2024: Report
news.para: Bengaluru and Mumbai saw the highest growth of 132% and 71% on a year-on-year basis, followed by Hyderabad and Kolkata.

news.title: BMC can levy water tax even if premises lie unused: Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court permits BMC to levy water tax and water benefit tax on property tax bills irrespective of water consumption. Yet, if water charges for actual consumption are paid, these taxes cannot be imposed additionally. The ruling originates from a case filed in 2005 involving Mars Enterprises over a south Mumbai property.
